Detailed Description

Holds information about a specific content provider.

This is returned by PackageManager#resolveContentProvider().

 // The following code shows how to check if the provider is Multiprocess.
 // assume that you have a PackageManager instance name pm.
 bool isProviderMultiprocess(String providerName, const PackageManager& pm){
   ProviderInfo pi;
   pi = pm.resolveContentProvider(providerName, 0);
   return pi.isMultiprocess();
 }

bool gaia::core::ProviderInfo::isMultiprocess ( ) const

Judge if the content provider support multiple process.

Returns:
If true, this content provider allows multiple instances of itself to run in different process. If false, a single instances is always run in getProcessName().
